A sleek, minimalist productivity tool built with a focus on clean architecture, modular styling, and responsive design. This project demonstrates the integration of Pug templates and SCSS preprocessing to create a maintainable front-end codebase.

🚀 Features
Dynamic Task Management: Add, complete, and delete tasks in real-time.

Persistent Storage: Uses localStorage to ensure your list remains even after a page refresh.

Responsive UI: Fully optimized for mobile, tablet, and desktop viewing.

Modular Styling: Built using SCSS variables and mixins for a consistent design system.

🛠️ Tech Stack
Templating: Pug (for clean, readable HTML structures).

Styling: SCSS (using nesting and variables for scalable CSS).

Logic: Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+).



🏗️ Architecture Highlight: SCSS & Pug
Instead of standard HTML/CSS, I chose a preprocessed workflow to simulate a professional environment:

Pug allowed me to write shorthand, error-free markup.

SCSS was utilized to create a themeable system. I used a primary color palette and flexbox mixins to ensure the UI stays "pixel-perfect" across devices.

🧠 The "Grit" Factor (Challenges Overcome)
The Challenge: Handling data persistence. Initially, the list disappeared on refresh.
The Solution: I implemented a JavaScript function to stringify the task array into JSON and store it in the browser's localStorage. I then wrote a "load" event listener to parse that data back into the UI when the app starts.

